race.comment: STAR VALOUR (3) has returned in terrific order off a long break, winning fresh at Lock before producing two strong chasing efforts here. Peaking now and keeps the claimer engaged. Looks the one to beat. DIDWEWIN (10) has warmed to her task late in both runs back and will relish the added trip. Already a winner here and is expected to be right there at the business end. MIDNIGHT RULER (5) never looked likely when getting too far back last time but gets the chance to settle closer here and gets weight relief with the 3kg claimer engaged. Watch for sharp improvement. BULLS ON PARADE (9) also benefits from weight relief and should be hitting his straps third-up. Not to be dismissed lightly.
